      <item>
        <title>Shiori by Example: Helpful Bootstrap Components</title>
        <description>&lt;p&gt;With Shiori, you can take advantage of all the available components in Bootstrap. Here are some useful components for blogging.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h2 id=&quot;buttons-and-font-awesome&quot;&gt;Buttons and Font Awesome&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Shiori automatically imports the latest version of &lt;a href=&quot;http://fortawesome.github.io/Font-Awesome&quot;&gt;Font Awesome&lt;/a&gt;. You can use it with &lt;code class=&quot;highlighter-rouge&quot;&gt;button&lt;/code&gt;s like so:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;button type=&quot;button&quot; class=&quot;btn btn-primary&quot;&gt;&lt;i class=&quot;fa fa-twitter&quot;&gt;&lt;/i&gt; Tweet&lt;/button&gt;
&lt;button type=&quot;button&quot; class=&quot;btn btn-default&quot;&gt;&lt;i class=&quot;fa fa-envelope-o&quot;&gt;&lt;/i&gt; Email&lt;/button&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h2 id=&quot;text-helpers&quot;&gt;Text Helpers&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;p&gt;You can use text helper classes to modify text easily. Documentations &lt;a href=&quot;http://getbootstrap.com/css/#helper-classes-colors&quot;&gt;here&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=&quot;http://getbootstrap.com/css/#type-alignment&quot;&gt;here&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p class=&quot;text-muted&quot;&gt;Use &lt;code&gt;text-muted&lt;/code&gt; to mute text color.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p class=&quot;lead&quot;&gt;Use &lt;code&gt;lead&lt;/code&gt; to for call-out text.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p class=&quot;text-center&quot;&gt;Use &lt;code&gt;text-center&lt;/code&gt; to center text.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h2 id=&quot;alerts&quot;&gt;Alerts&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;alert alert-success&quot; role=&quot;alert&quot;&gt;Alerts can be useful too!&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;h2 id=&quot;responsive-embed&quot;&gt;Responsive Embed&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Add &lt;code class=&quot;highlighter-rouge&quot;&gt;embed-responsive&lt;/code&gt; and either &lt;code class=&quot;highlighter-rouge&quot;&gt;embed-responsive-16by9&lt;/code&gt; or &lt;code class=&quot;highlighter-rouge&quot;&gt;embed-responsive-4by3&lt;/code&gt; classes to make embedded objects responsive.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;embed-responsive embed-responsive-16by9&quot;&gt;
&lt;iframe width=&quot;1280&quot; height=&quot;720&quot; src=&quot;//www.youtube.com/embed/J_vGbXDAvmQ?rel=0&quot; frameborder=&quot;0&quot; allowfullscreen=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;/iframe&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;h2 id=&quot;javascript-components&quot;&gt;JavaScript Components&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;p&gt;You can use all of the JavaScript components included by Bootstrap. Example: &lt;a data-toggle=&quot;modal&quot; data-target=&quot;#myModal&quot; href=&quot;#&quot;&gt;A modal dialog.&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;modal fade&quot; id=&quot;myModal&quot; tabindex=&quot;-1&quot; role=&quot;dialog&quot;&gt;
  &lt;div class=&quot;modal-dialog&quot;&gt;
    &lt;div class=&quot;modal-content&quot;&gt;
      &lt;div class=&quot;modal-header&quot;&gt;
        &lt;button type=&quot;button&quot; class=&quot;close&quot; data-dismiss=&quot;modal&quot;&gt;&lt;span aria-hidden=&quot;true&quot;&gt;&amp;times;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;sr-only&quot;&gt;Close&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/button&gt;
        &lt;h4 class=&quot;modal-title&quot;&gt;Modal Dialog&lt;/h4&gt;
      &lt;/div&gt;
      &lt;div class=&quot;modal-body&quot;&gt;
        &lt;p&gt;Hello World!&lt;/p&gt;
      &lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;
  &lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;h2 id=&quot;customizing-bootstrap&quot;&gt;Customizing Bootstrap&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Shiori uses &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/twbs/bootstrap-sass&quot;&gt;bootstrap-sass&lt;/a&gt;, so all of the variables are customizable. To learn more, check out Shiori’s &lt;a href=&quot;http://github.com/ellekasai/shiori/&quot;&gt;README&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
